{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":207,"text":"I'd like to reimagine education."},{"time":3558,"text":"The last year"},{"time":5148,"text":"has seen the invention of a new four-letter word."},{"time":8054,"text":"It starts with an M."},{"time":9967,"text":"MOOC: massive open online courses."},{"time":14424,"text":"Many organizations"},{"time":15901,"text":"are offering these online courses"},{"time":18659,"text":"to students all over the world, in the millions, for free."},{"time":22689,"text":"Anybody who has an Internet connection"},{"time":24249,"text":"and the will to learn can access these great courses"},{"time":26777,"text":"from excellent universities"},{"time":28871,"text":"and get a credential at the end of it."},{"time":32128,"text":"Now, in this discussion today,"},{"time":34752,"text":"I'm going to focus"},{"time":35987,"text":"on a different aspect of MOOCs."},{"time":39255,"text":"We are taking what we are learning"},{"time":41606,"text":"and the technologies we are developing in the large"},{"time":44171,"text":"and applying them in the small"},{"time":46271,"text":"to create a blended model of education"},{"time":49250,"text":"to really reinvent and reimagine"},{"time":51043,"text":"what we do in the classroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53470,"text":"Now, our classrooms could use change."},{"time":55980,"text":"So, here's a classroom"},{"time":58401,"text":"at this little three-letter institute"},{"time":60426,"text":"in the Northeast of America, MIT."},{"time":63210,"text":"And this was a classroom about 50 or 60 years ago,"},{"time":65529,"text":"and this is a classroom today."},{"time":68996,"text":"What's changed?"},{"time":72116,"text":"The seats are in color."},{"time":74663,"text":"Whoop-de-do."},{"time":77791,"text":"Education really hasn't changed"},{"time":80502,"text":"in the past 500 years."},{"time":82197,"text":"The last big innovation in education"},{"time":84528,"text":"was the printing press and the textbooks."},{"time":88010,"text":"Everything else has changed around us."},{"time":89420,"text":"You know, from healthcare to transportation,"},{"time":91243,"text":"everything is different,\nbut education hasn't changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95736,"text":"It's also been a real issue in terms of access."},{"time":98409,"text":"So what you see here"},{"time":100036,"text":"is not a rock concert."},{"time":102538,"text":"And the person you see at the end of the stage"},{"time":105084,"text":"is not Madonna."},{"time":107144,"text":"This is a classroom"},{"time":108773,"text":"at the Obafemi Awolowo University in Nigeria."},{"time":113191,"text":"Now, we've all heard of distance education,"},{"time":117127,"text":"but the students way in the back,"},{"time":118495,"text":"200 feet away from the instructor,"},{"time":120607,"text":"I think they are undergoing long-distance education."},{"time":125502,"text":"Now, I really believe"},{"time":127177,"text":"that we can transform education,"},{"time":129392,"text":"both in quality and scale and access,"},{"time":132238,"text":"through technology."},{"time":134546,"text":"For example, at edX,"},{"time":138241,"text":"we are trying to transform education"},{"time":140494,"text":"through online technologies."},{"time":143654,"text":"Given education has been calcified for 500 years,"},{"time":146913,"text":"we really cannot think about reengineering it,"},{"time":149104,"text":"micromanaging it."},{"time":150249,"text":"We really have to completely reimagine it."},{"time":152557,"text":"It's like going from ox carts to the airplane."},{"time":156598,"text":"Even the infrastructure has to change."},{"time":158121,"text":"Everything has to change."},{"time":159734,"text":"We need to go from lectures on the blackboard"},{"time":163099,"text":"to online exercises, online videos."},{"time":165707,"text":"We have to go to interactive virtual laboratories"},{"time":168188,"text":"and gamification."},{"time":169837,"text":"We have to go to completely online grading"},{"time":171748,"text":"and peer interaction and discussion boards."},{"time":174501,"text":"Everything really has to change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176782,"text":"So at edX and a number of other organizations,"},{"time":179288,"text":"we are applying these technologies to education"},{"time":181447,"text":"through MOOCs to really\nincrease access to education."},{"time":184633,"text":"And you heard of this example,"},{"time":186350,"text":"where, when we launched our very first course --"},{"time":188966,"text":"and this was an MIT-hard"},{"time":190732,"text":"circuits and electronics course --"},{"time":192320,"text":"about a year and a half ago,"},{"time":195014,"text":"155,000 students from 162 countries"},{"time":200317,"text":"enrolled in this course."},{"time":202020,"text":"And we had no marketing budget."},{"time":204706,"text":"Now, 155,000 is a big number."},{"time":208194,"text":"This number is bigger"},{"time":209933,"text":"than the total number of alumni of MIT"},{"time":212564,"text":"in its 150-year history."},{"time":216389,"text":"7,200 students passed the course,"},{"time":218547,"text":"and this was a hard course."},{"time":221010,"text":"7,200 is also a big number."},{"time":224464,"text":"If I were to teach at MIT two semesters every year,"},{"time":228006,"text":"I would have to teach for 40 years"},{"time":230883,"text":"before I could teach this many students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233485,"text":"Now these large numbers"},{"time":235023,"text":"are just one part of the story."},{"time":237181,"text":"So today, I want to discuss a different aspect,"},{"time":239843,"text":"the other side of MOOCs,"},{"time":241068,"text":"take a different perspective."},{"time":243247,"text":"We are taking what we develop\nand learn in the large"},{"time":246182,"text":"and applying it in the small"},{"time":247727,"text":"to the classroom, to create\na blended model of learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251723,"text":"But before I go into that, let me tell you a story."},{"time":256326,"text":"When my daughter turned 13, became a teenager,"},{"time":260410,"text":"she stopped speaking English,"},{"time":263777,"text":"and she began speaking this new language."},{"time":266838,"text":"I call it teen-lish."},{"time":269644,"text":"It's a digital language."},{"time":271856,"text":"It's got two sounds: a grunt and a silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278570,"text":"\"Honey, come over for dinner.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":281886,"text":"\"Hmm.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":283481,"text":"\"Did you hear me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":285615,"text":"Silence. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287878,"text":"\"Can you listen to me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":289250,"text":"&amp;quot;Hmm.&amp;quot;"}]},{"cues":[{"time":290622,"text":"So we had a real issue with communicating,"},{"time":292578,"text":"and we were just not communicating,"},{"time":294846,"text":"until one day I had this epiphany."},{"time":297860,"text":"I texted her. (Laughter)"},{"time":300523,"text":"I got an instant response."},{"time":302841,"text":"I said, no, that must have been by accident."},{"time":304526,"text":"She must have thought, you know,"},{"time":305613,"text":"some friend of hers was calling her."},{"time":307900,"text":"So I texted her again. Boom, another response."},{"time":310997,"text":"I said, this is great."},{"time":312806,"text":"And so since then, our life has changed."},{"time":314862,"text":"I text her, she responds."},{"time":316420,"text":"It's just been absolutely great."},{"time":318922,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324777,"text":"So our millennial generation"},{"time":326747,"text":"is built differently."},{"time":328381,"text":"Now, I'm older, and my\nyouthful looks might belie that,"},{"time":330882,"text":"but I'm not in the millennial generation."},{"time":334738,"text":"But our kids are really different."},{"time":336370,"text":"The millennial generation is completely comfortable"},{"time":338229,"text":"with online technology."},{"time":339469,"text":"So why are we fighting it in the classroom?"},{"time":341498,"text":"Let's not fight it. Let's embrace it."},{"time":343131,"text":"In fact, I believe -- and I have two fat thumbs,"},{"time":344820,"text":"I can't text very well --"},{"time":346469,"text":"but I'm willing to bet that with evolution,"},{"time":348636,"text":"our kids and their grandchildren"},{"time":350881,"text":"will develop really, really little, itty-bitty thumbs"},{"time":352711,"text":"to text much better,"},{"time":354094,"text":"that evolution will fix all of that stuff."},{"time":356954,"text":"But what if we embraced technology,"},{"time":358725,"text":"embraced the millennial generation's"},{"time":361329,"text":"natural predilections,"},{"time":362594,"text":"and really think about creating\nthese online technologies,"},{"time":365639,"text":"blend them into their lives."},{"time":367073,"text":"So here's what we can do."},{"time":368896,"text":"So rather than driving our kids into a classroom,"},{"time":371388,"text":"herding them out there at 8 o'clock in the morning --"},{"time":373960,"text":"I hated going to class at 8 o'clock in the morning,"},{"time":376718,"text":"so why are we forcing our kids to do that?"},{"time":378800,"text":"So instead what you do"},{"time":379974,"text":"is you have them watch videos"},{"time":381994,"text":"and do interactive exercises"},{"time":383805,"text":"in the comfort of their dorm rooms, in their bedroom,"},{"time":386494,"text":"in the dining room, in the bathroom,"},{"time":388355,"text":"wherever they're most creative."},{"time":390932,"text":"Then they come into the classroom"},{"time":392927,"text":"for some in-person interaction."},{"time":396351,"text":"They can have discussions amongst themselves."},{"time":398188,"text":"They can solve problems together."},{"time":399764,"text":"They can work with the professor"},{"time":400910,"text":"and have the professor answer their questions."},{"time":403904,"text":"In fact, with edX, when we\nwere teaching our first course"},{"time":407767,"text":"on circuits and electronics around the world,"},{"time":410193,"text":"this was happening unbeknownst to us."},{"time":412572,"text":"Two high school teachers"},{"time":414111,"text":"at the Sant High School in Mongolia"},{"time":417793,"text":"had flipped their classroom,"},{"time":419940,"text":"and they were using our video lectures"},{"time":422219,"text":"and interactive exercises,"},{"time":424092,"text":"where the learners in the high school,"},{"time":425703,"text":"15-year-olds, mind you,"},{"time":427288,"text":"would go and do these things in their own homes"},{"time":429122,"text":"and they would come into class,"},{"time":430469,"text":"and as you see from this image here,"},{"time":432405,"text":"they would interact with each other"},{"time":433491,"text":"and do some physical laboratory work."},{"time":435828,"text":"And the only way we discovered this"},{"time":437149,"text":"was they wrote a blog"},{"time":438572,"text":"and we happened to stumble upon that blog."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442595,"text":"We were also doing other pilots."},{"time":444702,"text":"So we did a pilot experimental blended courses,"},{"time":447184,"text":"working with San Jose State University in California,"},{"time":450156,"text":"again, with the circuits and electronics course."},{"time":452003,"text":"You'll hear that a lot. That course has become"},{"time":454471,"text":"sort of like our petri dish of learning."},{"time":457947,"text":"So there, the students would, again,"},{"time":460215,"text":"the instructors flipped the classroom,"},{"time":462942,"text":"blended online and in person,"},{"time":464663,"text":"and the results were staggering."},{"time":466971,"text":"Now don't take these results to the bank just yet."},{"time":469613,"text":"Just wait a little bit longer as we\nexperiment with this some more,"},{"time":472101,"text":"but the early results are incredible."},{"time":474262,"text":"So traditionally, semester upon semester,"},{"time":476659,"text":"for the past several years, this course,"},{"time":479000,"text":"again, a hard course,"},{"time":480689,"text":"had a failure rate of about 40 to 41 percent"},{"time":483805,"text":"every semester."},{"time":485305,"text":"With this blended class late last year,"},{"time":488003,"text":"the failure rate fell to nine percent."},{"time":491984,"text":"So the results can be extremely, extremely good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495747,"text":"Now before we go too far into this,"},{"time":498974,"text":"I'd like to spend some time discussing"},{"time":501626,"text":"some key ideas."},{"time":502775,"text":"What are some key ideas"},{"time":503986,"text":"that makes all of this work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":506843,"text":"One idea is active learning."},{"time":509070,"text":"The idea here is, rather than have students"},{"time":511510,"text":"walk into class and watch lectures,"},{"time":513696,"text":"we replace this with what we call lessons."},{"time":516738,"text":"Lessons are interleaved sequences"},{"time":518982,"text":"of videos and interactive exercises."},{"time":521663,"text":"So a student might watch a five-, seven-minute video"},{"time":524842,"text":"and follow that with an interactive exercise."},{"time":527882,"text":"Think of this as the ultimate\nSocratization of education."},{"time":531027,"text":"You teach by asking questions."},{"time":533007,"text":"And this is a form of learning"},{"time":534511,"text":"called active learning,"},{"time":535788,"text":"and really promoted by a very early paper, in 1972,"},{"time":539067,"text":"by Craik and Lockhart,"},{"time":540585,"text":"where they said and discovered"},{"time":542106,"text":"that learning and retention really relates strongly"},{"time":544486,"text":"to the depth of mental processing."},{"time":546235,"text":"Students learn much better"},{"time":547727,"text":"when they are interacting with the material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550915,"text":"The second idea is self-pacing."},{"time":553693,"text":"Now, when I went to a lecture hall,"},{"time":555329,"text":"and if you were like me,"},{"time":556619,"text":"by the fifth minute I would lose the professor."},{"time":558585,"text":"I wasn't all that smart, and I would\nbe scrambling, taking notes,"},{"time":562165,"text":"and then I would lose the lecture\nfor the rest of the hour."},{"time":565356,"text":"Instead, wouldn't it be nice with online technologies,"},{"time":567826,"text":"we offer videos and interactive\nengagements to students?"},{"time":571694,"text":"They can hit the pause button."},{"time":573425,"text":"They can rewind the professor."},{"time":575916,"text":"Heck, they can even mute the professor."},{"time":579015,"text":"So this form of self-pacing"},{"time":581069,"text":"can be very helpful to learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583694,"text":"The third idea that we have is instant feedback."},{"time":587048,"text":"With instant feedback,"},{"time":588525,"text":"the computer grades exercises."},{"time":590380,"text":"I mean, how else do you teach 150,000 students?"},{"time":592675,"text":"Your computer is grading all the exercises."},{"time":594969,"text":"And we've all submitted homeworks,"},{"time":596503,"text":"and your grades come back two weeks later,"},{"time":598544,"text":"you've forgotten all about it."},{"time":600168,"text":"I don't think I've still received\nsome of my homeworks"},{"time":602245,"text":"from my undergraduate days."},{"time":603730,"text":"Some are never graded."},{"time":605077,"text":"So with instant feedback,"},{"time":606571,"text":"students can try to apply answers."},{"time":608061,"text":"If they get it wrong, they can get instant feedback."},{"time":610470,"text":"They can try it again and try it again,"},{"time":612118,"text":"and this really becomes much more engaging."},{"time":614051,"text":"They get the instant feedback,"},{"time":615634,"text":"and this little green check mark that you see here"},{"time":618553,"text":"is becoming somewhat of a cult symbol at edX."},{"time":622143,"text":"Learners are telling us that they go to bed at night"},{"time":625047,"text":"dreaming of the green check mark."},{"time":628491,"text":"In fact, one of our learners"},{"time":630293,"text":"who took the circuits course early last year,"},{"time":633074,"text":"he then went on to take a software course"},{"time":635006,"text":"from Berkeley at the end of the year,"},{"time":637307,"text":"and this is what the learner had to say"},{"time":639453,"text":"on our discussion board"},{"time":640725,"text":"when he just started that course"},{"time":642251,"text":"about the green check mark:"},{"time":644772,"text":"&amp;quot;Oh god; have I missed you.&amp;quot;"},{"time":646829,"text":"When's the last time you've seen students"},{"time":649527,"text":"posting comments like this about homework?"},{"time":653988,"text":"My colleague Ed Bertschinger,"},{"time":656384,"text":"who heads up the physics department at MIT,"},{"time":658554,"text":"has this to say about instant feedback:"},{"time":661398,"text":"He indicated that instant feedback"},{"time":664399,"text":"turns teaching moments into learning outcomes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670174,"text":"The next big idea is gamification."},{"time":672466,"text":"You know, all learners engage really well"},{"time":674367,"text":"with interactive videos and so on."},{"time":675876,"text":"You know, they would sit down and shoot"},{"time":677141,"text":"alien spaceships all day long until they get it."},{"time":679485,"text":"So we applied these gamification\ntechniques to learning,"},{"time":682272,"text":"and we can build these online laboratories."},{"time":684495,"text":"How do you teach creativity?\nHow do you teach design?"},{"time":686752,"text":"We can do this through online labs"},{"time":688421,"text":"and use computing power"},{"time":689698,"text":"to build these online labs."},{"time":691287,"text":"So as this little video shows here,"},{"time":693675,"text":"you can engage students"},{"time":695140,"text":"much like they design with Legos."},{"time":696747,"text":"So here, the learners are building a circuit"},{"time":698665,"text":"with Lego-like ease."},{"time":700556,"text":"And this can also be graded by the computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704647,"text":"Fifth is peer learning."},{"time":707581,"text":"So here, we use discussion forums and discussions"},{"time":710416,"text":"and Facebook-like interaction"},{"time":712516,"text":"not as a distraction,"},{"time":714380,"text":"but to really help students learn."},{"time":717227,"text":"Let me tell you a story."},{"time":718944,"text":"When we did our circuits course"},{"time":722170,"text":"for the 155,000 students,"},{"time":724036,"text":"I didn't sleep for three nights"},{"time":725701,"text":"leading up to the launch of the course."},{"time":727588,"text":"I told my TAs, okay, 24/7,"},{"time":730147,"text":"we're going to be up"},{"time":731413,"text":"monitoring the forum, answering questions."},{"time":733287,"text":"They had answered questions for 100 students."},{"time":735260,"text":"How do you do that for 150,000?"},{"time":738121,"text":"So one night I'm sitting up there, at 2 a.m. at night,"},{"time":740457,"text":"and I think there's this question"},{"time":741678,"text":"from a student from Pakistan,"},{"time":743649,"text":"and he asked a question, and I said,"},{"time":744977,"text":"okay, let me go and type up an answer,"},{"time":746433,"text":"I don't type all that fast,"},{"time":748041,"text":"and I begin typing up the answer,"},{"time":749605,"text":"and before I can finish,"},{"time":751299,"text":"another student from Egypt\npopped in with an answer,"},{"time":753973,"text":"not quite right, so I'm fixing the answer,"},{"time":755891,"text":"and before I can finish, a student from the U.S."},{"time":757859,"text":"had popped in with a different answer."},{"time":759468,"text":"And then I sat back, fascinated."},{"time":762268,"text":"Boom, boom, boom, boom, the students were"},{"time":764215,"text":"discussing and interacting with each other,"},{"time":766166,"text":"and by 4 a.m. that night, I'm totally fascinated,"},{"time":768684,"text":"having this epiphany,"},{"time":770152,"text":"and by 4 a.m. in the morning,"},{"time":771408,"text":"they had discovered the right answer."},{"time":773161,"text":"And all I had to do was go and bless it,"},{"time":774888,"text":"\"Good answer.\""},{"time":776854,"text":"So this is absolutely amazing,"},{"time":779206,"text":"where students are learning from each other,"},{"time":781016,"text":"and they're telling us that they are learning"},{"time":783833,"text":"by teaching."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786130,"text":"Now this is all not just in the future."},{"time":788110,"text":"This is happening today."},{"time":789862,"text":"So we are applying these blended learning pilots"},{"time":792179,"text":"in a number of universities and \nhigh schools around the world,"},{"time":794920,"text":"from Tsinghua in China"},{"time":796706,"text":"to the National University of Mongolia in Mongolia"},{"time":799138,"text":"to Berkeley in California --"},{"time":800749,"text":"all over the world."},{"time":802108,"text":"And these kinds of technologies really help,"},{"time":804132,"text":"the blended model can really help"},{"time":805681,"text":"revolutionize education."},{"time":807779,"text":"It can also solve a practical problem of MOOCs,"},{"time":811190,"text":"the business aspect."},{"time":812870,"text":"We can also license these MOOC courses"},{"time":815186,"text":"to other universities,"},{"time":816925,"text":"and therein lies a revenue model for MOOCs,"},{"time":819489,"text":"where the university that\nlicenses it with the professor"},{"time":821878,"text":"can use these online courses"},{"time":823715,"text":"like the next-generation textbook."},{"time":825916,"text":"They can use as much or as little as they like,"},{"time":828371,"text":"and it becomes a tool in the teacher's arsenal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833857,"text":"Finally, I would like to have you"},{"time":835907,"text":"dream with me for a little bit."},{"time":838748,"text":"I would like us to really reimagine education."},{"time":842917,"text":"We will have to move from lecture halls to e-spaces."},{"time":847042,"text":"We have to move from books to tablets"},{"time":849717,"text":"like the Aakash in India"},{"time":851543,"text":"or the Raspberry Pi, 20 dollars."},{"time":853891,"text":"The Aakash is 40 dollars."},{"time":855898,"text":"We have to move from\nbricks-and-mortar school buildings"},{"time":858812,"text":"to digital dormitories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861433,"text":"But I think at the end of the day,"},{"time":862881,"text":"I think we will still need one lecture hall"},{"time":865123,"text":"in our universities."},{"time":867685,"text":"Otherwise, how else do we tell our grandchildren"},{"time":870509,"text":"that your grandparents sat in that room"},{"time":873904,"text":"in neat little rows like cornstalks"},{"time":877128,"text":"and watched this professor at the end"},{"time":879681,"text":"talk about content and, you know,"},{"time":882328,"text":"you didn't even have a rewind button?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":884975,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887203,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":889194,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}